The root cause of the bug is in the line:
Using StringBuilder
Alternatively, we can use a 'StringBuilder' to build the combined string. Here's the modified code:
```java
StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
for (String value : values) {
    if (sb.length() > 0) {
        sb.append(", ");
    }
    sb.append(value);
}
header(name, sb.toString());
```
This will also correctly handle multiple values for the same header and pass the test.
